# CI Workflow Script Separation

## Rules
- Keep workflow YAML declarative (triggers, jobs, permissions, sequencing).
- Keep simple one-liners inline; extract non-trivial shell logic to scripts.
- Extract immediately when logic adds branching, retries, repeated command groups, or reduced readability.
- Place CI scripts in stable versioned paths (for example: `scripts/ci/`).
- Reuse shared scripts instead of duplicating command blocks across jobs.
- Keep script interfaces explicit via arguments/env vars and validate required inputs early.
- Keep scripts deterministic and non-interactive.
- Keep step names short and action-oriented (for example: `Run Tests`); keep extra context in logs/docs.
